02/05/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan hinted on Saturday (1 May) that his government might formally recognise the Greek Cypriot state. "The world has recognised Greek Cyprus, what can you do by saying 'I do not recognise it'," Erdogan told reporters before leaving for EU celebrations in Dublin. Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul says no decision has been made.
In other news, Turkish Cypriot Prime Minister Mehmet Ali Talat is to meet with US Secretary of State Colin Powell this week. Washington is reviewing its policies on northern Cyprus following Turkish Cypriot support of a UN plan to reunify the island. Greek Cypriots rejected the blueprint. (AFP, MPA, ANA - 30/04/04)
